Enum OmxLookup.Dim

    OmxLookup<D,C>

    public static enum OmxLookup.Dim
extends java.lang.Enum<OmxLookup.Dim>
    The DIM enum is used to specify which dimension a lookup applies to. It corresponds to the dim attribute in the omx file.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FIRST
      The first dimension.
      NOT_SPECIFIED
      The dimension is not specified.
      SECOND
      The second dimension.

      • getDimValue

        public int getDimValue()
        Get the integer value used in the omx file for indicating the dim attribute. For NOT_SPECIFIED, this method will return -1; this value should not be saved in the omx file, as it is invalid (no dime attribute should be set in this case).
        Returns:
        the integer value for the omx file dim attribute
